execline
--------

Binaries are installed in /usr/lib/execline/bin. So if you want to write
execline scripts, please extend your PATH with /usr/lib/execline/bin before
using them.

Please see the reason at <https://bugs.debian.org/906250>.

However for convenience, a script is provided as /usr/bin/execlineb,
which adds /usr/lib/execline/bin/ to PATH when invoked. So you can use
/usr/bin/execlineb as shebang for your scripts.

 -- Shengjing Zhu <zhsj@debian.org>  Sun, 13 Oct 2019 17:45:16 +0800
